article.headline: Pennsylvania 79, Brown 62
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber scored 22 points on 9 of 12 shooting and Tim Begley scored 13 of his 22 points in the second half to lead Penn to a 79-62 victory over Brown on Friday night, the Quakers' 11th straight win. The victory extended the Quakers' (15-7, 8-0 Ivy) win streak to 11 games. Keenan Jeppersen's nine points led Brown (9-12, 2-5) as Penn held Jason Forte to eight points and four shots from the field. Brown trailed by as many as 14 points in the first half (27-13) before staging a 13-4 run in the final six minutes before intermission. Penn led 31-26 at halftime. Begley hit three 3-point shots in the opening moments of the second half, helping the Quakers reel off 14 unanswered points for a 58-34 lead with 9:45 remaining. Mark Zoller added 14 points and collected 12 rebounds for Penn.
